Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setHierFlowMode(25.10)                                  setHierFlowMode(25.10)

Name
       setHierFlowMode  - Allows setting umbrella options for the hierarchical
       flow

Syntax
       setHierFlowMode

       [-help]

       [-budgets {accurate | preliminary | none}]

       [-reset]

       Allows setting umbrella options for  the  hierarchical  flow.  Use  the
       -budget  parameter of this command to set the budgeting mode parameters
       of the setBudgetingMode command for accurate or preliminary budgeting.

       In case a setBudgetingMode parameter is already  set  in  the  database
       with  a  preferred  or non-preferred value, the setHierFlowMode command
       will not reset it to its preferred value. Therefore, use  setBudgeting-
       Mode  -reset  before using the setHierFlowMode command, to reset to de-
       fault values.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each setHierFlowMode parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setHierFlowMode

       -budgets {accurate | preliminary | none}
              Sets the budgeting mode parameters of the setBudgetingMode  com-
              mand  for  accurate or preliminary budgeting, as specified. Fol-
              lowing are the possible values of this parameter:

              * accurate: Sets all the setBudgetingMode parameters, which  are
                recommended  for  accurate budgeting. It is recommended not to
                use this value with stage-based or cycle-based budgeting.

              * preliminary: Sets all the setBudgetingMode  parameters,  which
                are  recommended  for preliminary budgeting. It is recommended
                to use this value with stage-based or cycle-based budgeting.

              * none: Does not set any setBudgetingMode parameter.

              * The -budgets parameter has lower precedence than the specified
                setBudgetingMode settings, irrespective of the order.

              * setHierFlowMode -budgets accurate |  preliminary  followed  by
                setHierFlowMode  -budgets none will not have any impact on any
                setBudgetingMode settings.

              Default: none

       -reset Resets all or specified parameters to the default value.

Example
              * The following command sets budgeting mode options of the  set-
                BudgetingMode command for accurate budgeting:

                setHierFlowMode -budgets accurate

                Following is the output of the above command:

                setHierFlowMode -budgets accurate

                ##INFO:  Setting following budgeting mode options for accurate
                budgeting:

                setBudgetingMode -handleComplexSdc  true

                ## INFO : Please set this  if  reduced  netlist  is  used  for
                blocks.

                ## setBudgetingMode -handleComplexSDC false

                ## Additionally, if regular expressions are used in SDC or in-
                teractive  constraints  specified by user along with a reduced
                netlist, please contact Cadence support.

                setBudgetingMode -masterClone merged

                setBudgetingMode -forceNetworkLatencyIncluded false

                setBudgetingMode -virtualClock false

                setBudgetingMode -useBoundaryCondition actual

              * The following command resets the value of the -budgets parame-
                ter to its default value none:

                setHierFlowMode -reset

Related Information
